<h1>Lightning Talks</h1>

<div class="grid_4 alpha feature">
       <p><a href = "https://twitter.com/dariocravero" target="_blank"><img src="./images/galway/dario.jpeg" alt="Darío Javier Cravero"  width="120" height="120"></a></p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid_4 feature">
        <p><strong>Darío Javier Cravero</strong> is CTO and co-founder at <a href="http://contentkingdom.co/" target="_blank">Content Kingdom</a> in Galway. He previously was Web Innovator & Co-Founder at UXtemple, CTO at Ex-Ordo, CTO at Starlight Solutions. He is core contributor to the <a href="http://www.padrinorb.com/" target="_blank">Padrino Web Framework</a> which is one of the most popular Ruby frameworks. He won the awards titled Best New Web Application/Service and Best Practices at the Irish Web Awards in 2011. He is also a volunteer coach for Rails Girls Galway 2014. </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid_4 omega feature">
        <p>Talk Topic: <strong>How and Why to enter an Open Source Community</strong>. </p>
      </div>

<hr />

<div class="grid_4 alpha feature">
       <p><a href = "https://twitter.com/DorothyCreaven" target="_blank"><img src="./images/galway/dorothy.jpeg" alt="Dorothy Creaven"  width="120" height="120"></a></p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid_4 feature">
        <p><strong>Dorothy Creaven</strong> is co-founder and CEO of <a href="http://elementwave.com/" target="_blank">Element Software</a> in Galway. In a short time, she has piloted the company from being a small start-up to winning Ireland's largest business competition (Seedcorn), winning public tender contracts, and signing significant deals with multinational customers, such as Sage and Ericsson. She is an electronic engineering graduate of NUIG and has worked for big names, such as Google and Abbott Vascular. Included in the <a href="http://www.siliconrepublic.com/careers/item/37203-wit2014" target="_blank">Top 100 women in STEM list by SiliconRepublic</a> and in the <a href="http://technologyvoice.com/2013/10/06/ireland%E2%80%99s-technology-women-yet-another-talented-38" target="_blank">Ireland’s Technology Women: Yet Another Talented 38 list by Technology Voice</a>. </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid_4 omega feature">
        <p>Talk Topic: <strong>Women in Entrepreneurship</strong>. </p>
      </div>


<hr />



<div class="grid_4 alpha feature">
       <p><a href = "https://twitter.com/catherinecronin" target="_blank"><img src="./images/galway/catherine.jpeg" alt="Catherine Cronin"  width="120" height="120"></a></p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid_4 feature">
        <p><strong>Catherine Cronin</strong> is Academic Coordinator of online IT programmes at the National University of Ireland, Galway, as well as a lecturer and online facilitator in both BSc and MSc programmes. Her work is focused on online and open education, digital literacies and social media in education.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid_4 omega feature">
        <p>Talk Topic: <strong>IT Education and Gender Divide</strong>. </p>
      </div>


<hr />




<div class="grid_4 alpha feature">
       <p><a href = "http://twitter.com/sparklyparticle" target="_blank"><img src="./images/galway/alanna.jpg" alt="Alanna Kelly"  width="120" height="120"></a></p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid_4 feature">
        <p><strong>Alanna Kelly</strong> is an experienced software engineer. She worked for over 6 years in the top tier game development studio "PopCap Games". She is currently a Research Assistant at INSIGHT Centre for Data Analytics, NUIG working on <a href="http://www.gambas-ict.eu" target="_blank">Gambas</a>, a Generic Adaptive Middleware for Behavior-driven Autonomous Services. She is also an electronics hacker and railway modeler. As a stable member and advocacate of the Galway-based <a href="" target="_blank">091labs hackerspace</a> she run several programming and electronic-related workshops. She is the organizer of the popular <a href="https://twitter.com/GalwayGameJam" target="_blank">Galway Game Jam</a> and a volunteer coach at both Rails Girls Galway 2013 and 2014. </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid_4 omega feature">
        <p>Talk Topic: <strong>Game Crafting</strong>. </p>
      </div>


<hr />




<div class="grid_4 alpha feature">
       <p><a href = "https://twitter.com/bnighrogain" target="_blank"><img src="./images/galway/bianca.jpg" alt="Bianca Ní Ghrógáin"  width="120" height="120"></a></p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid_4 feature">
        <p><strong>Bianca Ní Ghrógáin</strong> teaches at Griffeen Valley Educate Together National School, where she is extremely passionate about the use of technology as a pedagogical tool. She currently integrates educational technology into all areas of her teaching and her children’s learning. She is a maker, a learning technologist, a gaelgóir, a human rights education tutor and an eternal student.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid_4 omega feature">
        <p>Talk Topic: <a href="http://www.makeymakey.com/" target="_blank"><strong>MaKey MaKey</strong></a>: an Invention Kit for Everyone </p>
      </div>
      


<hr />



<div class="grid_4 alpha feature">
       <p><a href = "https://twitter.com/mtryle" target="_blank"><img src="./images/galway/maire.jpg" alt="Máire Ryle"  width="120" height="120"></a></p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid_4 feature">
        <p><strong>Máire Ryle</strong> attended Rails Girls Galway 2013 and is now a volunteer coach for Rails Girls Galway 2014. She changed her career path from being a Critical Care Nurse to undertaking the Higher Diploma in Business Systems Analysis. She also completed a Software developer Traineeship and after achieving the Irish Times Digital Marketing Diploma she became involved in the launch of Muldoon Whiskey, a new Waterford product; helping develop their website and digital strategy. Currently involved in business development with Ryle + Company.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid_4 omega feature">
        <p>Talk Topic: <strong>Career Path Change</strong>.</p>
      </div>



<hr />

<h1>Workshop Program</h1>


<a name="schedule"></a>
<div class="grid_12 alpha feature">

  <div class="grid_5 alpha" style="padding:5px 5px 5px 5px; background-color: #bebebe; border:1px solid; border-radius:10px;width:200px">
    <h3 style="color:#000">Schedule: Friday, June 20, 2014 6pm - 8pm</h3>
      <div style="padding:5px 5px 5px 5px; background-color: #fff;  border:1px solid; border-radius:10px;">
        <h4 style="color:#000;"><strong>18pm - 20pm</strong></h4>
        <h3>Installation Party</h3>
        <ul class="list-unstyled">
          <li><b>Bring your laptop</b> so we can help you install 
              Ruby&nbsp;on&nbsp;Rails and everything else you'll need
              using the <a href="http://guides.railsgirls.com/install/">
              INSTALL GUIDE.</a></li>
          <li>If there is no way you can make it on  Saturday 
              and need help with installation make arrangements
              to come at 9am on Saturday. We want to keep exceptions 
              to the bare minimum  Please be respectful of our 
              volunteer coaches' time.       <br />           <strong>Where:</strong> <a href="http://www.insight-centre.org" target="_blank">Insight Centre for Data Analytics</a> (ex DERI building), first floor</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <br />

   
   
  </div>

  <div class="grid_5 push_1 omega" style="padding:5px 5px 5px 5px; background-color: #bebebe; border:1px solid; border-radius:10px;width:650px">
    <h3 style="color:#000">Schedule: Saturday, June 21, 2014 9 am - 6 pm</h2>

      <div  style="padding:5px 5px 5px 5px; background-color: #fff;  border:1px solid; border-radius:10px;">
        <h4 style="color:#000;"><strong>9 am - 10 am</strong></h4>
        <h3>Registration</h3>
        <p>Register, find your seat, get your name tag and meet some people. </p>
        <h3>Late Installations</h3>
        <p>If you are absolutely not able to attend the Installation
          Party on Saturday we will get your computer ready to roll.
          <br />Please be here by 9am.</p>
      </div>

      <br />

      <div  style="padding:5px 5px 5px 5px; background-color: #fff;  border:1px solid; border-radius:10px;">
        <h4 style="color:#000;"><strong>10 - 10.20am</strong></h4>
        <h3>Welcome</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>What will we do/learn today? What will we develop?</li>
            <li>Sponsors</li>
          </ul>
      </div>

      <br />

      <div  style="padding:5px 5px 5px 5px; background-color: #fff;  border:1px solid; border-radius:10px;">
        <h4 style="color:#000;"><strong>10.20 am - 11 am</strong></h4>
        <h3>Workshop</h3>
          <p>We split into small groups. Each group is supervised by a coach who helps you to
              get started on your first web application using the <a
              href="http://guides.railsgirls.com/app/">app guide</a>
          </p>
<h3>Web Applications</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>what are they? (explanation)</li>
		<li>let's start developing one (hands-on)</li>
		<li>what are libraries? (explanation) - Keith Cortis</li>
		<li>let's use them! (hands-on)</li>
                <li>how are web apps structured? Bentobox (explanation)</li>
		<li>let's generate our own structure (hands-on)</li>
	</ul>
      </div>

      <br />

  <div  style="padding:5px 5px 5px 5px; background-color: #fff;  border:1px solid; border-radius:10px;">
        <h4 style="color:#000;"><strong>11.00 am - 11.10 am</strong></h4>
        <h3>Break</h3>
      </div>

      <br />

      <div  style="padding:5px 5px 5px 5px; background-color: #fff;  border:1px solid; border-radius:10px;">
        <h4 style="color:#000;"><strong>11.00 am - 12.30 am</strong></h4>
        <h3>Programming</h3>
	
	<ul>
		<li>Overview, Ruby and Ruby on Rails (explanation) - Stefania Farrugia</li>
		<li>let's dive into the code we've used so far (hands-on)</li>
                <li>MVC and HTML (explanation)</li>
		<li>let's improve our design (hands-on)</li>
	</ul>
      </div>

      <br />

      <div  style="padding:5px 5px 5px 5px; background-color: #fff;  border:1px solid; border-radius:10px;">
        <h4 style="color:#000;"><strong>12.30 am - 1.00 am</strong></h4>
        <h3>GitHub</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>what is it? (explanation) - Kevin Lyda</li>
		<li>let's create our first account and project (hands-on)</li>
	</ul>
      </div>

      <br />

      <div  style="padding:5px 5px 5px 5px; background-color: #fff;  border:1px solid; border-radius:10px;">
        <h4 style="color:#000;"><strong>1 pm - 2 pm</strong></h4>
        <h3>Lunch</h3>
          <p>Reward yourself for a successful morning with some grub. Talk
            with your coaches and peers about how awesome your first web
            applications are.</p>
	<h3>Lightning Talks</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>Game Crafting - Alanna Kelly</li>
		<li>IT in Education - Catherine Cronin</li>
		<li>MaKey Makey - Bianca Ní Ghrógáin</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <br />

      <div  style="padding:5px 5px 5px 5px; background-color: #fff;  border:1px solid; border-radius:10px;">
        <h4 style="color:#000;"><strong>2 pm - 3 pm</strong></h4>
<h3>App extension: Autism-friendly Tourism in Galway</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>what are the single components? (explanation) - Myriam Leggieri</li>
		<li>start working on the component assigned to your group (hands-on)</li>
		<li>push each contribution on our shared GitHub account</li>
	</ul>
      </div>

      <br />
  <div  style="padding:5px 5px 5px 5px; background-color: #fff;  border:1px solid; border-radius:10px;">
        <h4 style="color:#000;"><strong>3 pm - 4 pm</strong></h4>
<h3>Continuous Deployment</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>what are unit tests? (explanation)</li>
		<li>let's create our test cases (hands-on)</li>
		<li>how to apply continuous deployment on GitHub (explanation)</li>
		<li>let's do it! (hands-on)</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<br />

  <div  style="padding:5px 5px 5px 5px; background-color: #fff;  border:1px solid; border-radius:10px;">
        <h4 style="color:#000;"><strong>4 pm - 4.30 pm</strong></h4>
<h3>Lightning Talks</h3>
	<ul>
		<li> Entrepreneurship - Dorothy Creaven</li>
		<li>Career Change - Máire Ryle</li>
        </ul>
<h3>Break</h3>
 </div><br />

  <div  style="padding:5px 5px 5px 5px; background-color: #fff;  border:1px solid; border-radius:10px;">
        <h4 style="color:#000;"><strong>4.30 pm - 5.30 pm</strong></h4>
<h3>Cloud Deployment</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>Microsoft Azure and OpenShift (explanation) - Gerry Kavanagh</li>
		<li>let's publish our app online! (hands-on)</li>
        </ul>
</div>
      <br />

      <div  style="padding:5px 5px 5px 5px; background-color: #fff;  border:1px solid; border-radius:10px;">
        <h4 style="color:#000;"><strong>5.30 pm - 6 pm</strong></h4>
<h3>Show of everyone's work<h3>
<h3>Where to go from here</h3>
<h3>Awards celebration<h3>
</div>
<br />
      <div  style="padding:5px 5px 5px 5px; background-color: #fff;  border:1px solid; border-radius:10px;">
        <h4 style="color:#000;"><strong>6.00 pm - 8 pm</strong></h4>
        <h3>Afterparty at Westwood</h3>
          <p>Reward yourself for a successful day with a tasty beverage and
             treats. Network and chat with coaches and peers. <br />  Westwood is just across the road from the workshop venue.
          </p>
      </div>
